<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Midwife" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Midwife,</orth> a woman who assists other women in childbirth: <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.62" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 62</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 2, 141</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. III, 1, 11</bibl>. Term of contempt for an old woman: <cit><quote>does it work upon him? Like aqua vitae with a m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 215</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with Lady Margery, your m. there,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.160" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 160</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>